WEBVTT

00:03.187 --> 00:08.534
I said, I want to live in the back of my pickup truck. 
And I have a camper, and I've got a little bed in

00:08.554 --> 00:14.482
there, and I've got a little cooler that I put ice 
in. And I said, you know, I can shower and shave at

00:14.502 --> 00:21.491
the handball courts because I was playing 
handball every chance I got. And he said, well, you

00:22.392 --> 00:26.157
can't be in B1. He says, if you're not in the 
barracks, you can't be in B1. So he says, I'll go

00:31.790 --> 00:39.017
talk to Colonel Baker, but you'll have to go into 
the H1. I said, sir, that's a married company. He

00:40.699 --> 00:44.182
says, well, you'll be the only bachelor in the 
married company then. And he says, the only other

00:44.803 --> 00:51.230
thing you've got to do is you've got to go get 
written permission from the campus security.

00:52.331 --> 00:57.696
Because when I go to Colonel Baker, I want it to be 
OK. And so I went, and the campus security was in the

00:57.980 --> 01:03.687
OYMCA, down in the basement to the right. And there 
was three people in the campus security. You know,

01:07.471 --> 01:12.818
I mean, there may have been four or five, but there 
was never more than three policemen there. And I

01:13.378 --> 01:18.204
went in there and I said, look, this is, and I laid 
out my plan. Well, I know they knew that this was not

01:18.985 --> 01:22.329
going to last. There's no way, you know, anybody 
would stay in a pickup truck forever in the camper.

01:28.405 --> 01:34.191
But, you know, they checked, and I had never had 
one, no parking tickets. I had not had one incident

01:34.311 --> 01:36.814
on the campus. And I told them I was working with my 
advisor, and I was in the Corps and everything. So

01:44.482 --> 01:48.807
he wrote out a handwritten little note, and I took 
it up to Captain Simmons. And he said, where do you

01:49.788 --> 01:53.351
want to stay? Where are you going to park this 
thing? And I said, well, I'd like to park it in the

01:54.993 --> 01:57.636
same place. And they said, well, and so we talked 
about it. And I don't know if he suggested or I

02:02.400 --> 02:10.567
suggested, but there was an oak tree behind Guyon 
Hall that provided good shade. And so I kind of, for

02:11.108 --> 02:16.512
some reason, would always get that parking lot, 
parking spot. But I parked in Guyon Hall. I

02:18.854 --> 02:26.481
showered and shaved when I was here at the handball 
courts. And I studied at the library. And you were

02:28.582 --> 02:30.065
taking a full course load. Oh, yeah. And I was in the 
core. And nobody came by and rattled the pickup?

02:35.334 --> 02:37.398
No, the only thing that would... It was kind of 
interesting. One January, maybe in January of 67,

02:39.361 --> 02:46.354
I don't know, I had... I usually face the truck to 
the north, but that, for some reason, I faced the

02:47.043 --> 02:51.610
truck to the south. I guess I had a different 
parking space. And an ice storm came up, and it was a

02:54.174 --> 02:57.139
world-class ice storm. And my pickup, to get out of 
my camper, above the pickup, you just open the top,

02:57.720 --> 03:08.477
and then you had to open that, and you jumped out. I 
mean, it didn't have a door. It just had an opening.

03:11.462 --> 03:13.185
Well, it was iced shut. And I'm sitting there 
kicking on it, you know, trying to get out because I

03:13.958 --> 03:18.925
got to go to class. And somebody came by and said, 
there's somebody in the back of that truck. And I

03:24.933 --> 03:26.775
hollered at them. And so they got something hard 
and chipped the ice and I got out. And then

03:34.766 --> 03:38.411
sometimes the parking lot would be filling. And 
what would happen, I'd go to the farm and I'd work

03:43.844 --> 04:01.764
especially in the spring, till, you know, dark, 8 
or 9 o'clock, and then I'd come, and instead of

03:43.844 --> 04:01.764
spending the night, if I had an 8 o'clock class, and 
I'd come back, and it'd be 10 or 11 o'clock by the

03:43.844 --> 04:01.764
time I'd get in, I'd go right to bed, and then I'd set 
the alarm. Well, people would hear the alarm go off

04:01.824 --> 04:08.511
sometime, and I'd hear them say, I heard an alarm, 
and then, you know, you would meet. And my bed, you

04:08.812 --> 04:11.995
couldn't sit up in my bed. you had to roll out of bed. 
If you sat up, you hit your head. And then, you know,

04:15.608 --> 04:21.115
you were on your knees, and so I had a cushion in 
there with a carpet. And then, you know, I kept my

04:21.996 --> 04:30.065
uniforms in there and put my Aggie boots on every 
day and pulled them off by myself and shined them.

04:30.085 --> 04:31.867
Now, you ate at Dunkin'? Well, no. Once I stopped 
rooming board, I ate at the Kettle. which was on

04:38.570 --> 04:42.900
Highway 6, which is now a donut shop across from 
Luby's. But it was called The Kettle, and I ate all

04:43.722 --> 04:51.921
my meals there, and they had a blackboard off to the 
side, and everybody knew that that's where I ate,

04:52.947 --> 04:55.751
and that was my message board. People would come in 
and write me a message and say, because we didn't

04:56.212 --> 05:09.412
have cell phones, I didn't have a phone, I didn't 
have a phone at the ranch, and they could wait

04:56.212 --> 05:09.412
around, they knew where I parked, but they would 
write me notes. And so when I ate, I ate at the

05:09.612 --> 05:16.963
kettle, and I knew everybody in there, and that was 
my message board for a year and a half. Now, as we're

