16:33.286 --> 16:38.778
know, if two Aggies can't figure this out, it can't 
be figured out. And it would kind of break the ice,

16:38.818 --> 16:47.015
you know, and it was just, you know, and Pat Gamble 
was the PACAF commander at the time. And a couple of

16:47.055 --> 16:49.260
times we were in some tough meetings. And there 
would be a break and there'd be friction and

16:49.882 --> 16:59.692
everything else and Bear and Pat and I would just 
kind of get together in a car and he says, you know,

16:49.882 --> 16:59.692
if three Aggies can't figure this out, it can't be 
figured out. And we'd go back into this meeting and

17:00.313 --> 17:09.102
solve what would be a problem for the President of 
the United States or the Secretary of Defense or

17:00.313 --> 17:09.102
the Secretary of State and we would solve it. And so 
I think the Aggie spirit is just experiences where

17:17.759 --> 17:24.147
